<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Supports Peaceful Solution to Iraqi Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam Thursday voiced supports
for a peaceful solution to the Iraqi crisis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a regular press conference, a spokesman for the
Vietnamese Foreign Ministry said Vietnam welcomes and supports all
efforts from the international community to find a peaceful
solution to the crisis for the sake of peace and stability in
the region and the world.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam is following the situation with deep concern, the
spokesman added, and Vietnam holds that military measures can not
resolve the problem, but would make it more tense and
complicated.
</P>
<P>
The latest crisis over Iraq began when Iraqi President Saddam
Hussein refused to allow the United Nations weapons inspectors to
check some 60 sites, including some 40 presidential palaces, on
ground of national sovereignty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
