<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Hopes to Strengthen Ties With Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, February 5 (Xinhua) -- China hopes to further
strengthen relations with Spain, a senior Chinese official said
here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Spanish Second Deputy Prime Minister Rato
Figredo, Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing said that China and Spain
share identical or similar views on many world issues and the
Chinese government wishes to join hands with the Spanish
government in building a long-term, stable and friendly
relationship.
</P>
<P>
Li suggested that Chinese and Spanish businessmen should
actively explore new areas and methods for cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Figredo praised the rapid growth of the Chinese economy and
expressed the conviction that bilateral relations will be further
strengthened and developed.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that Spain will stick to the "one-China policy"
on the question of Taiwan and supports an early entry of China
into the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived in Madrid Wednesday evening for a four-day official
visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
