<HEADLINE> Refugees Registration Causes Difference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 5 (Xinhua) -- A registration by United
Nations High Commission for Refugees (UNHCR) at a camp in
southwestern Uganda caused some arguments from the benefiters, a
report reaching here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hans Thoolen, the UNHCR representative in Uganda, said the
registration is a normal measure to record the number of refugees
to whom the UNHCR relief its supplies.
</P>
<P>
The UNHCR made wrist bands and ink on refugees.
</P>
<P>
But the 1160 Congolese refugees of Rwandan origin argued that
it means to them, according to their custom, a spell doom and
they had refused the marks in January.
</P>
<P>
The measure is aimed at prevention of repeated registration
and get the supplies more targeting, Thoolen explained in his
statement.
</P>
<P>
But he added the methods of registration may be vary depending
on the number of refugees in an area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
