<HEADLINE> Torrential Rain Causes Flooding in Northern Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rain Thursday caused
flooding and damage to some parts of northern Greece.
</P>
<P>
In the towns of Kavala, Drama and surrounding areas, more than
200 homes have been flooded and agricultural fields inundated by
waters from the swelling Angitis and Drama rivers, the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
