<HEADLINE> Flights Canceled as Farmers Block Roads to Crete </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 5 (Xinhua) -- All flights at Crete's Heraklion
airport had to be canceled Thursday as angry farmers used their
cars to block the roads to the airport.
</P>
<P>
Before blocking access to the airport, farmers from the Greek
prefectures of Heraklion, Rethymno and Lasithi gathered outside
the offices of the Federation of Agricultural Associations of
Heraklion prefecture, waving black flags to show their opposition
to the government policies of tight spending, according to the
semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) Thursday.
</P>
<P>
After that gathering, farmers marched through the center of
Heraklion to the airport, causing serious traffic problems.
</P>
<P>
In recent days, thousands of farmers have taken their tractors
onto the motorway linking Athens and northern Greece to pressure
the government to meet their demands including higher prices for
their products and an end to production quotas and penalties
imposed by the European Union. 
