<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia's Duma Approves 1998 Budget in Third Reading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Russia's State Duma, lower house
of parliament, today approved the 1998 draft budget on its third
reading by 232 votes for and 141 against, with one abstention,
according to ITAR-TASS.
</P>
<P>
The budget bill is still awaiting the fourth and final readings
on February 11.
</P>
<P>
The draft budget envisages revenues of 367.5 billion
redenominated rubles (61.3 billion US dollars) and expenditures of
499.9 billion rubles (83.3 billion dollars). The GDP is planned at
2,840 billion rubles (473.3 billion dollars) and annual inflation
at 5.7 percent, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The allowed maximum of budget deficit has been set at 132.4
billion rubles (22 billion dollars) or 5.7 percent of the GDP.
</P>
<P>
Duma speaker Gennady Seleznyov said after the voting, "It will
be extremely difficult for the government to fulfill this budget."
"For this government it is practically unrealizable," he said.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma endorsed the 1998 budget draft bill in its first
reading on December 5, 1997, and in its second reading on December
25, 1997. 
</P>
