was a member of parliament and demanded to take pictures of the
troops on the Botswana side of the river.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministry statement said the platoon commander of
Botswana defense force said he had not been informed about the
Namibian visit.
</P>
<P>
Ownership of few islands have become a bone of contention
between Botswana and Namibia during the past years. These are
Situngu, Luyondo and Kasikili islands situated in the Linyanti
and Chobe rivers on the Namibian side of the border.
</P>
<P>
