<HEADLINE> Nigeria Set for Massive Retrenchment of Civil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, February 5 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government will
soon start a massive retrenchment of its civil servants by at
least 30 percent, with the recent issue of of a guideline for the
exercise.
</P>
<P>
The government explained the guideline in a circular dated
January 23 and signed by Alhaji Gidado Idiris, the secretary to
the federal government, the News Agency of Nigeria said in a
report Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The circular gives the rate of retrenchment in each level of
the positions and listed offences for which officials could be
rationalized.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, such offences include dishonesty,
drunkenness, false claims against the government, falsification
and suppression of records, or failure to keep records, among
others.
</P>
<P>
Those who were appointed irregularly, or belonging to secret
cults, or suffering from prolonged ill-health will also lose
their jobs, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian government announced the massive retrenchment of
civil servants last December. 
