on Thursday reasserted his innocence over allegations of sexual
impropriety made against him, saying the charges are "false."
</P>
<P>
During a photo session in the Oval Office at the start of a
visit by British Prime Minister Tony Blair, Clinton said the
charges that he had an improper relationship with former White
House intern Monica Lewinsky, are "false."
</P>
