export from 2 billion dollars to 5.2 billion dollars for every six
months so that it can buy more daily necessities.
</P>
<P>
But Iraq, which has been under a sanction for its invasion of
Kuwait in 1990, is incapable of exporting so much oil now, said
some oil experts.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi-U.N. "Oil for Food" agreement is the sole exception
to the U.N.-imposed embargo. 
