<HEADLINE> Chinese Workers Get Unemployment Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, February 6 (Xinhua) -- An unemployment insurance
system has been established in this capital of north China's
Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Taiyuan's unemployment insurance
scheme has covered 2,771 enterprises and 670,000 employees, with
the coverage rate reaching 100 percent for state-owned enterprises
and 85 percent for privately owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
To date the city's unemployment insurance institutions have
granted 25.57 million yuan in unemployment relief fund.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment insurance system has played a positive role in
helping enterprises ride out financial difficulties and in
promoting re-employment among displaced workers.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment insurance agencies have also given out 6.06
million yuan in special funds that have been used to train 32,000
laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
The beneficiaries of the unemployment insurance system were
mostly previous employees of financially troubled enterprises that
have suspended operation for more than six months in aggregate or
three consecutive months, and employees who have failed to receive
a salary for more than six months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
