be further enhanced through the visit, Obuchi said in a meeting
with Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan. (Japan-China-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ULAN BATOR -- Mongolia on Friday published its first law which
will govern the stationing in and passing through its territory of
foreign troops.
</P>
<P>
Under the new law adopted by the Great Hural (parliament) on
January 8, Mongolia may invite foreign troops to station in its
territory if the country is under foreign armed aggression or is
in a de facto state of such aggression.
</P>
<P>
Foreign troops may also be deployed in Mongolia if the United
Nations Security Council has passed a resolution authorizing the
use of the U.N. peacekeeping force. (Mongolia-Military Law)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
expressed the hope Friday for a peaceful solution to the current
Iraqi crisis, but adding Israel reserves the right of self-defense
if attacked.
</P>
<P>
In an official briefing on the Persian Gulf situation held
here to foreign diplomats based in Israel, Netanyahu said Israel
is "hopeful that there will be a peaceful solution to the present
crisis."
</P>
<P>
He voiced Israel's full support to the United States and the
international community in demanding Iraq to allow unfettered
search by U.N. inspectors of weapons of mass destruction.
(Israel-Iraq-Netanyahu Speech) 
