<HEADLINE> Thai Boxer Samson Retains WBF Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Samson Dutchboygym of Thainland
retained his World Boxing Federation (WBF) junior bantamweight
title by stopping Philippines' Felix Marfa here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Samson knocked out the challenger at one minute 45 seconds in
the fourth round in the 22nd title defence.
</P>
<P>
Samson took command with left and right hooks to the head and
body, attacking mercilessly in the fourth round with a long series
blows that eventually dropped the Filippino in the corner.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Samson improved to 27 wins with 24 knockouts
while Marfa dropped to 23 wins and seven losses. 
</P>
