<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suspects in Fatal Alcohol Poisoning Case Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Two suspects have been arrested
and 33 others detained for their involvement in the poisonous
alcohol case in north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
According to local police, an illegal wine-maker in Wenshui
County produced the fatal drinks by mixing 2,400 kilograms of
methanol with 24,000 kilograms of alcohol and sold the mixture.
</P>
<P>
The buyer then mixed the dangerous drinks with other additives
and wholesaled it to private shops in Shuozhou and Datong cities.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 222 people were hospitalized from drinking the
mixture; 27 people have died, while 171 have been discharged from
hospitals.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the State Bureau for Technical
Supervision has ordered its local branches to take emergency
measures to prevent the spread of the fatal drinks.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities in some northern and northeastern provinces
have begun to check on any suspicious alcoholic drinks from
Shanxi. People have been advised not to drink bulk or bottled
alcohol with the label of "Zhongxing Brewery, Xinghua Village,
Fenyang City, Shanxi Province." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
