<HEADLINE> German Wind Power Industry Ranks First in World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Germany has become the world's
leader in wind power production with an installed capacity of
2,075 megawatts last year.
</P>
<P>
The United States, which used to rank first in wind power
production, had 1,600 megawatts of installed capacity in 1997,
said a report of the International Forum for Regenerative
Energies, a research unit linked to the Muenster University.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that wind power has become the second most
important regenerative energy source in Germany after
hydroelectric power.
</P>
<P>
Last year, wind power generation in Germany reached 3 billion
kilowatt-hours, up from 2.2 billion in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sales of wind generators rose by 4 percent to 833 in 1997 in
Germany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
