<HEADLINE> Qualifications Affirmed for Deputies to Ninth NPC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The Deputies Qualifications
Examination Committee of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC) today held a meeting at the Great Hall of
the People to examine the qualifications of 2,980 deputies to the
Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
The deputies were elected to represent provinces,
municipalities, autonomous regions, Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) and the People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
The committee affirmed the qualifications of all deputies based
on the Electoral Law for the National People's Congress and the
Local People's Congress; the PLA Electoral Rule on deputies to the
NPC and the People's Congress Above County Level; the Decisions at
the Fifth Session of the Eighth NPC on the Number and Election of
Deputies to the Ninth NPC; the Hong Kong SAR's Electoral Rule on
Deputies to the Ninth NPC; the Distribution Plan on the Number of
Deputies to the Ninth NPC for Ethnic Groups, which was approved by
the Standing Committee of NPC; the Consultative Electoral Rule of
Taiwan Province on Deputies to the Ninth NPC; and other related
laws.
</P>
<P>
Because of the death of Liu Lit-For, a deputy elected by the
Hong Kong SAR on Jan. 29, the number of the deputies to the Ninth
NPC is now 2,979.
</P>
<P>
This examination result will be submitted to the 30th session
of the Standing Committee of the Eighth NPC for confirmation, and
then the names of all the deputies will be announced. 
</P>
