<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, State President
and General Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China, has express deep concern for those who fell ill
and died from drinking unlawfully made alcohol in north China's
Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
During the Spring Festival, more than 20 people died and
hundreds were hospitalized in Shuozhou after drinking the
poisonous alcoholic beverages that were illegally produced in
Wenshui County of Shanxi.
</P>
<P>
A suspect has been arrested while the case is still under
investigation. Meanwhile, local governments are trying to minimize
the loss.
</P>
<P>
Jiang reportedly was shocked when he received an emergency
report about the case on Jan. 31.
</P>
<P>
He said that greater efforts should be made to control market
activities and crack down on manufacturing and trading of fake
products to safeguard the public.
</P>
<P>
Jiang has instructed legal departments to severely punish
lawbreakers who have been involved in making and dealing in
illegal alcoholic drinks. 
