<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Sixty-one members of a
charity fund-raising team from Hong Kong arrived at their
destination here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The members of the Walk-to-Guangzhou activity sponsored by Hong
Kong Sowers Action were officially welcomed at Taihe Square. The
group aims to raise 20 million Hong Kong dollars to aid children
living in the mountainous areas of the Chinese inland to go to
school.
</P>
