<HEADLINE> World Business Group to Tighten Ties With UN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Vice-president of the
International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) Adnan Kassar left here
Friday for New York for talks designed to strengthen the chamber's
relations with the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Kassar, accompanied by a delegation of economists and
businessmen, will meet U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan on how to
enhance private sector involvement in U.N. development projects
worldwide.
</P>
<P>
He will also discuss with UN officials different ways of
strengthening administrative procedures, particularly for small
industries.
</P>
<P>
The ICC, established in 1920 in Paris, is a worldwide
organization with an aim to promote trade and economic exchanges
in the world.
</P>
<P>
Kassar, also the president of Lebanese Chamber of Commerce,
will take advantage of the visit to meet U.S. businessmen,
particularly the leading American businessmen of Lebanese origin,
to encourage their involvement in Lebanon's post-war
rehabilitation process.
</P>
<P>
He will end up his visit in Washington, meeting with
International Bank and International Finance Corporation
representatives over possible funding for a number of Lebanese
private sector enterprises. 
</P>
