<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 43.73
points, or 0.42 percent, to close at 10,485.86 Friday.
</P>
<P>
The shares of commerce and industry, properties, utilities
and finance gained 0.59 percent, 0.91 percent, 0.76 percent and
0.99 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, H shares -- China's state-owned enterprises listed
on the Hong Kong bourse -- grew 6.66 percent and red chips rose
3.39 percent.
</P>
<P>
Friday's turnover was 10,364 million HK dollars (1,329 million
U.S. dollars), a growth of 3,374 million HK dollars (433 million
U.S. dollars) from Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index opened at 10,580.45 points in the morning,
a growth of 138.32 points, or 1.32 percent, from the close of the
previous trading day.
</P>
<P>
The shares rose 140.10 points, or 1.34 percent, to close at
10,582.23 at midday.
</P>
<P>
The stocks gained 139.52 points, or 1.35 percent, to close at
10,442.13 Thursday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
