<HEADLINE> Dalian Sanyo Sets Record Per Capita Output Value </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The Dalian Sanyo Refrigeration
Co. Ltd. equalled the standards of the world's top 500 companies
with a 1997 per-capita output value of 1.8 million yuan (217,000
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
In addition, the company's per-capita profits for the year hit
350,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Sanyo, the largest company of its kind in China, was
jointly established by the Dalian Bingshan (Icehill) Group, and
Sanyo Electric Co. Ltd. and Nissoho Iwai Co. of Japan, in October
1993.
</P>
<P>
The company's net profits for the first three years of
operations stood at 120 million yuan, with all partners recouping
their initial investments during the period.
</P>
<P>
The company led Dalian's 6,000 Sino-foreign joint ventures in
terms of overall performance, in addition to ranking as Sanyo's
leading foreign branch.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese partners invested an additional two billion
Japanese yen in March 1997 to set up a second refrigeration co. in
Dalian, a major port city of northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
</TEXT>
