<HEADLINE> 8 Killed, 41 Injured in North India Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 6 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people were
killed and 41 others injured when a bus fell into a gorge near
Malnu of Himachal Pradesh in northern India Friday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said the bus was carrying more than 50
passengers. So far four bodies have been recovered from the
wreckage of the bus. There could be more bodies in the wreckage as
some persons trying to jump out of the bus were carried along by
the rolling vehicle.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-nine seriously injured passengers were rushed to a
nearby hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is yet to be known.  
</P>
