<HEADLINE> Explosion Rocks Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 6 (Xinhua) -- A strong bomb exploded in the
center of the Sri Lankan capital Friday afternoon, killing at
least seven people and injuring many others.
</P>
<P>
The blast took place only two days after the country celebrated
the 50th Independence Day on Wednesday, on which President
Chandrika Kumaratunga vowed to do everything to end terrorism and
war in her country.
</P>
<P>
Police said the incident took place when security forces in the
Downtown area stopped a van for routine check.
</P>
<P>
They said a woman suspect and two men were inside the van when
the blast rocked the city.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place near an air force camp which is only a
few blocks away from Galadari Hotel and Hilton Hotel, which
sustained serious damage when a massive truck-bomb exploded last
October.
</P>
<P>
Among the dead were two security personnel, local reports said.
</P>
<P>
The extent of damage was not quite serious, according to the
Capital Radio Station.
</P>
<P>
Police have sealed off the scene and the suspects have not been
identified yet.  
</P>
</TEXT>
