<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Figures Consulted On Report Draft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng presided over a
discussion in Beijing today to consult leaders of non-communist
parties and noted figures with no party affiliation on the draft
of the government work report to be submitted to the upcoming
First Session of the Ninth National People's Congress, due on
March 5.
</P>
<P>
He Luli, Ding Shisun, Cheng Siwei, Xu Jialu, Jiang Zhenghua,
Luo Haocai, Wang Wenyuan, Zhang Kehui, Zhang Xuwu, Cheng Siyuan
spoke at the meeting, expressing their views on the report.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the past five years have witnessed great
achievements made by the Chinese people of all nationalities in
the socialist modernization drive, under the leadership of the
Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
The report has summed up, in a manner of seeking truth from
facts, the achievements and basic experience obtained during the
past five years, and made a serious analysis on the existing
problems, they held.
</P>
<P>
The noted non-Communist figures were satisfied with the
framework of the draft and proposed certain revisions regarding
agriculture, enterprise reform, education, environmental
protection, anti-corruption, social security, financial
supervision and control, institutional reform and
poverty-elimination.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li Peng thanked the speakers for their useful comments
and he also expressed his gratefulness to them for their care and
support to the government during the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Non-communist leaders and figures attending today's discussion
also included Lei Jieqiong, Wang Guangying, Qian Weichang, Sun
Fuling, Wang Guoquan and Zhou Tienong.
</P>
<P>
Vice premiers Zhu Rongji, Qian Qichen, Wu Bangguo, Jiang
Chunyun, State Councilor Luo Gan, and Wang Zhaoguo, Vice-Chairman
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference National
Committee, joined today's panel discussion.  
</P>
