<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate during the
October-December period last year in Macao dropped to 2.7
percent, latest Statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released Friday by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that the jobless rate in the last three months of
1997 was 0.2 percent down from the September-November period.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate in the October-December period was also 1.1
percent lower from the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate stood at 0.7 percent, down 0.2 percent
from the September-November period.
</P>
<P>
Previous statistics said that in the third quarter of 1997,
Macao had about 6,300 jobless people. The overall labor population
was estimated at 206,300 out of its 415,000 residents.
</P>
<P>
Macao has seen an economic slowdown since 1993. The economic
growth rate for 1997 was estimated at less than one percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
