<HEADLINE> European Balloonists Break World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- A three-man European ballooning
trio on Friday beat the 12-year-old world record for the longest
non-stop flight without refuelling, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The old mark of nine days and four minutes, which was
established in 1986 by U.S. aviator Dick Rutan and his Voyager
airplane, was overturned by the trio in the Breitling Orbiter 2
Balloon.
</P>
<P>
The balloon is now heading for a landing in Myanmar where the
crew planned to complete their flight which began January 28 at
Chateau-d'Oex, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The balloon was about to come down in plains near the ancient
town of Bago, 80 kilometer from Myanmar's capital Yangon. 
</P>
