<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandans Prefer Contract Marriage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- A research has found that many
Ugandans prefer contract marriage.
</P>
<P>
Enid Nambuya, a member of Uganda Association of Women Lawyers,
said at a domestic violence workshop Wednesday that a survey in
eastern districts of Kampala, Iganga and Soroti and western
district of Masindi indicated that spouses were easier to deal
with their problems under contract marriage.
</P>
<P>
The interviewees of the survey include women and men in
intimate relationship, victims of domestic violence, law
enforcement officers and health workers.
</P>
<P>
They want more strict law dealing with physical abuses,
Nambuya said.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said there are few cases of contract marriages
and divorces among local spouses for the time being.
</P>
<P>
Domestic violence is still widespread in the country,
especially in rural areas, they noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
