<HEADLINE> Kenyatta University Closed Indefinitely </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's Kenyatta University
was ordered closed indefinitely on Thursday evening after
students demonstrated against the killing of a former colleague
in Nakuru District, the Daily Nation reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said the angry students staged
demonstrations in the university compound before they barricated
the busy Thika-Nairobi highway from 2:30 p.m..
</P>
<P>
About 8,000 students boycotted classes Thursday, demanding
President Daniel arap Moi's resignation over politically-
instigated violence in parts of the Rift Valley Province.
</P>
<P>
The students gave the Kenyan government 48 hours to stop the
on-going killings in Njoro, Laikipia and Nakuru, or they will "make
Nairobi city ungovernable", the paper said.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by Vice-Chancellor George Eshiwani of the
university said that following the anti-social acts of some
students along the Thika-Nairobi highway, the senate of the
university had decided to close the university with immediate
effect.
</P>
<P>
Riot police and General Service Unit were sent and camped a
kilometer away from the university gate along the highway. No
clashes were reported between students and policemen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
