<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Chen Jinhua, minister in charge
of the State Planning Commission, today called for greater efforts
to improve the government's ability and methods for implementing
macroeconomic controls during the current transition from the
planned to a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China currently faces various difficulties and
challenges involving economic restructuring and the reform of
state enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the remarks during the on-going International Workshop
on Social Development in China's Economic Transition Period.
</P>
<P>
He called on governments at all levels to work hard to ensure a
stable and relaxed social environment for economic reform and
urged them to explore a workable policy system for social
affairs and a management model with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Chen stressed that the Chinese government has persistently
supported the United Nations in its efforts to promote worldwide
development and peace. China has started a number of co-operative
projects in the social development sector with some countries and
such cooperation will accelerate on the principle of equality and
mutual benefit, he said..
</P>
<P>
Hao Jianxiu, vice-minister in charge of State Planning
Commission, said in the workshop that China has recorded
monumental achievements in social development in recent years.
</P>
<P>
She added that the country must adopt effective policies,
measures and management mechanisms to provide more job
opportunities and eliminate poverty.
</P>
<P>
The three-day workshop is sponsored by the State Planning
Commission and the United Nations Development Program. More than
90 Chinese and foreign officials and scholars are attending the
event.  
</P>
