<HEADLINE> Chinese Specialists Refute US Human Rights Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese human rights
specialists and scholars pointed out here today that the China
Part of "1997 Human Rights Report" issued by the US State
Department on January 30 has once again interfered with China's
internal affairs under the pretext of human rights.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar on the US Human Right Report, they pointed out
that by distortion and fabrication and citing the so-called
"facts", the report made unwarranted charges with China's human
rights situation.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Muzhi, president of China Society for Human Rights Studies,
said that although the report admitted that China has made some
progress in human rights, it continues to ignore the facts and
justice here in China.
</P>
<P>
The greatest achievement China has made in the field of human
rights is its success in providing adequate food and clothing for
its 1.2 billion people and in its efforts to help more than 50
million people to get out of poverty.
</P>
<P>
Other participants noted at the seminar that the United States
issues a human rights report every year, violating basic
international norms and the current tide of progress in the world,
thus meeting the resistance and opposition from more and more
countries.
</P>
<P>
"The United States should halt its overbearing move of
interfering the internal affairs of other countries by using
the human rights issue," participants stressed.
</P>
<P>
More details are to follow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
