<HEADLINE> 22 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-two rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in armed
clashes with the Turkish security forces in southeastern Turkey
Thursday, an official statement said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the security forces and the PKK militants clashed
in the towns of Nusaybin and Midyat in Mardin province. Three
security soldiers were also killed and two others wounded in the
clashes, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It added that in another development, the security forces
shot dead five PKK guerrillas at Homek Tepe area of Lice
town of Diyarbakir province. But the statement failed to say
when the PKK rebels were killed.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the security forces have captured one
PKK militant in Diyarbakir province and two PKK militants
surrendered to the security forces in the same province.
</P>
<P>
Over 28,000 people including the PKK rebels, civilians and
government troops have been killed in eastern and southeastern
Turkey since the PKK started fighting for autonomy in August
1984. 
</P>
