<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The Kruger National Park,
the largest game reserve in South Africa, will celebrate 100
years of conservation next month, park officials said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
To celebrate the birthday of the park, leaders of the lcoal
communities, Kruger Park staff and guests will hold a massive
party and launch a one-year long program to promote conservation
in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
A series of educational programs will spread the conservation
message and commemorative videos detailing the history of the
park will be produced, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
