<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Close Slightly Weaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market
closed slightly weaker Friday, despite solid interest in major
industrials News Corp. and Coca Cola Amatil.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed down 1.8 points to 2656.1 after
Wall Street shed 12.46 points to close at 8,117.25.
</P>
<P>
The market was quiet ahead of the release of profit reports, a
stockbroker at a local firm said.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index finished down 1.9 points, or 0.16
percent, to 1174.9 and the all industrials closed down 1.8
points, or 0.04 percent, to 4519.1.
</P>
<P>
The banking index closed up 13.8 points or 0.26 percent at
5353.8, with major banks closing higher.
</P>
<P>
National Australia bank gained 18.4 cents to 19.75 Australian
dollars, ANZ bank lifted nine cents to 9.74 dollars while Westpac
bank added 1.7 cents to 9.938 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among resource stocks, major diversified miner BHP gained 21
cents to 15.07 Australian dollars, WMC rose four cents to 5.32
dollars and Rio Tinto lost 24 cents to 19.56 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The gold index fell 11.4 points, or 0.98 percent, to 1155.4
after gold bullion weakened slightly. Gold closed in Sydney at
298.25 U.S. dollars, down 20 cents from Thursday's close.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 300.96 million lots, valued at 561
million U.S. dollars. Falls narrowly outnumbered rises 526 to 525.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
