<HEADLINE> African-American Alliance Encourages Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- African, African-American
Alliance plans to create a 150-million-U.S. Dollar equity fund
and a 500-million-Dollar fund to encourage investment and
development in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The alliance will also seek to provide a forum for activities
to promote economic opportunity and socio-cultural exchange
between Africans and African-Americans on the continent and
throughout the diaspora, said a press release of the alliance.
</P>
<P>
"Trends in the world market indicate that countries will have
to engage in more resource and information sharing. Competition
can only be won from a global approach," the press release noted.
</P>
<P>
Other components within the alliance include the creation of a
free zone between Africa and the Unites States and visa system to
guard against routing goods through other nations to avoid
quotas,local newspaper Daily Mail reported today.
</P>
<P>
This partnership with Africa will create market access,
foreign debt concessions and technology transfer, it added.
</P>
<P>
The alliance will have a business discussion on Friday with
representatives from the Zambia Chambers of Commerce and
Industry, Zambia Privatization Agency, Export Board of Zambia and
the Zambia Investment Centre on topics such as export, America's
current policy toward Africa and privatization. 
