<HEADLINE> EU Signs Angolan Reconstruction Aid Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
signed an agreement with Angola under which the EU will offer 100
million U.S. Dollars in aiding Angola's national reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Prime Minister Franca van-Dunem and the visiting Joao
de Deus Pinheiro,the EU official in charge of EU's Africa,
Caribbean and Pacific Affairs signed the agreement on behalf of
their respective sides.
</P>
<P>
Van-Dunem said at the signing ceremony Thursday that the newly
signed agreement would be very important in the post-war Angola
reconstruction and development and it would encourage countries to
fulfill their promise for the country's reconstruction made on
the 1995 Brussel meeting.
</P>
<P>
EU's move has showed, Van-Dunem said, that it is standing on
Angola's side in its national reconciliation effort.
</P>
<P>
Pinheiro said that Angola should unite all Angolans and the
friendly countries in its opening up a new page for the war-torn
country.
</P>
<P>
Pinheiro arrived in Luanda Thursday for a three-day visit
which is focused on EU's relation with Angola in its
reconstruction. 
