<HEADLINE> France's Population Attains 60.9 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 6 (Xinhua) -- France's population attained 60.9
million by January 1, 1998, said the official statistics office
INSEE Friday.
</P>
<P>
The population of France proper attained 58.7 million, an
increase of 231,000 persons over the previous year, said INSEE.
</P>
<P>
The number of new-born babies were 725,000 in 1997, down from
735,300 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The number of people who died in 1997 were 534,000, also down
from 536,800 in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The rate of infant mortality stood at 5.1 per thousand,
compared with 4.9 per thousand in 1996 and 1995.
</P>
<P>
Life expectancy for men is 74.2 years, and that for women is
82.1 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
