<HEADLINE> Pearl Orchids Bring More Income to Chinese Farmers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Huang Chuanxian, a formerly
poor Qianjiang County resident in the southwest China municipality
of Chongqing, earned 30,000 yuan (3,600 US dollars) in 1997, a
dramatic rise on his former annual income of only 2,000 yuan (241
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
"Growing pearl orchids enabled my family to escape poverty,"
said Huang with a broad smile.
</P>
<P>
Pearl orchids, a wild flower species found in the country's
southwestern mountainous areas, have also brought prosperity to
poverty-stricken people in the Tujia Minority Autonomous County in
the Chongqing area.
</P>
<P>
Pearl orchids, a type of herbal plant, make an excellent
"gourmet powder" for flower tea. However, harsh weather conditions
inhibit the growth of the delicate species.
</P>
<P>
Since 1988, the Qianjiang County tea processing plant has
cooperated with the Southwest Agriculture University to expand
plantation areas for the plant. The cooperative effort led to the
establishment of pearl orchid processing venture.
</P>
<P>
The current annual output of flower tea containing pearl orchid
ingredients stands at one million tons, with related products
earning profits of 3.5 million yuan (422,000 US dollars). The
products are exported to Japan and India, and are sold in a number
of cities and eight provinces, including Anhui, Fujian and Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
Tea experts predict that pearl orchid flower tea will become an
important component in China's flower tea family.
</P>
<P>
Pearl orchids are currently grown on 667,000 hectares in
Qianjiang County. Growing the flowers has enabled some 600
families in seven towns become better off, with total income for
the group approaching five million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Projections for the year 2000 call for the company to produce
2,000 tons of tea. Some 10,000 farmers families from 40-odd towns
will be growing pearl orchids, and earnings from related
activities will soar to 40 million yuan (4.8 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980206.0191 </DOCNO>
