<HEADLINE> Five Countries to Make Debut at Winter Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAGANO, Japan, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Athletes from five countries
of Azerbaijan, Macedonia, Kenya, Venezuela and Uruguay will have their
first sip of snow and ice at winter Olympics.
</P>
<P>
According to the Nagano Organizing Committee (NAOC), skiiers and
skaters from those countries will make their debut at the 18th Olympic
Winter Games, which will open on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
To take part in winter Olympics will be a long-lasting memory for
those athletes.
</P>
<P>
Gabriel Hottegindre, the only competitor of the one-man Uruguay
team, could not keep in his joy. "I am so happy to come here for the
winter Olympics. I have never imagine it," he said.
</P>
<P>
"My aim here is to compete," the Alpine skiier said.
</P>
<P>
His coach Anole Bachlera shared the happiness of Hottegindre. "I
have been in professional contact with Gabriel for about eight years
when Uruguay asked me to take care of him in Nagano Olympics, the
first one for Uruguay," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I am very proud of it," he added.
</P>
<P>
The registration of the five countries increased the total
participants at the games to 72, which set a record in winter Olympic
history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
