<HEADLINE> China Fulfils 1997 Target of Agricultural Taxes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- China collected a total of
39.66 billion yuan (4.78 billion US dollars) in agricultural taxes
in 1997, 1.3 times the planned figure, according to statistics
from the State Administration of Taxation.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural taxes for 1997 grew by 2.76 billion yuan, up 7.46
percent on the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
China's agriculture sector had a good harvest in 1997, with
grain output hitting 492.5 million tons, the second highest level
in history, and cotton output standing at 4.3 million tons,
100,000 tons more than the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
The animal husbandry and fisheries sectors also witnessed
steady growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
