<HEADLINE> Local Regulations Being Used To Stop China's "White Pollution" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The environmental protection
bureau of Shanghai will develop regulations to reduce the use of
styrofoam for food containers.
</P>
<P>
The regulation will increase controls on production and
recycling of products that use styrofoam, leading ultimately to
replacements.
</P>
<P>
China introduced production lines for styrofoam containers in
1984, leading to a sharp increase in their use, and because of the
difficulties it posed in the natural environment, the styrofoam
contains are usually referred to as "white pollution". 
</P>
