<DOCNO> XIE19980206.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing's Finances Developing Well, Report Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's financial sector did
well in 1997, contributing to local economic growth, Beijing Daily
reported today.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, total savings deposits in Beijing were up
86.28 billion yuan (10.4 billion US dollars) from the beginning of
the year.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, banks and other financial organizations made
investments of 4.76 billion yuan (573.5 million US dollars) in
state key enterprises and large-scale firms, put an extra 3.96
billion yuan (477.1 million US dollars) into agricultural
projects, and an additional 13.46 billion yuan (1.62 billion US
dollars) into technological renovation and infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Local banks loaned 2.78 billion yuan (334.9 million US dollars)
for housing projects and 7.97 billion yuan (960 million US
dollars) for commercial projects, and also loaned 20.75 million
yuan (2.5 million US dollars) to local unemployed workers in
1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
