<HEADLINE> Guatemala Forces 1-1 Tie with Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Guatemala forced a 1-1 draw
with four-time world champions Brazil in the group match of the
Gold Cup soccer tournament on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Star striker Romario converted a penalty kick in the 79th
minute to put Brazil ahead 1-0 after he was fouled by second-half
substitute Engelvert Herrera at the top of the penalty box.
</P>
<P>
Juan Carlos Plata became the hero for Guatemala four minutes
into injury time when he headed home a corner kick by captain
Martin Machon at the Orange Bowl in Miami, Florida.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilians could have made it 3-1 had two goals not been
called back because of offside calls, one by Romario at the 23rd
minute and another by Zinho at the 43rd.
</P>
<P>
Brazil was without several key players, including Ronaldo,
Rivaldo, Aldair and Juninho.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will meet El Salvador in its third and final first-round
match in Los Angeles on Sunday. 
</P>
