DHAKA -- The Bangladeshi government will launch a six-day
national leprosy elimination campaign in October this year to
detect about 40,000 leprosy patients in the country and bring
them under the treatment program, the independent United News
Bangaldesh (UNB) reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The campaign will create a national awareness on leprosy, with
the aim of achieving the goal of eliminating leprosy by the year
2000. (Bangladesh-Leprosy)
</P>
