employees in Beijing-based foreign enterprises, according to a
government official.
</P>
<P>
The official said 8,000 foreigners and 220,000 Chinese paid
individual income tax last year, but the latter accounted for 28
percent of the total amount. (China-Beijing-Individual Income Tax)
</P>
