</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A Russian official has denounced allegations made in
a U.S. State Department report on human rights. Gennady Tarasov,
director of the foreign ministry's press bureau, said Thursday
that the U.S. report failed to take into consideration Russia's
democratic progress.
</P>
<P>
The report, Tarasov said, which is similar to previous ones, is
full of flaws. He said the report evaluates the Russian human
rights situation according to American laws and practices.
</P>
<P>
Tarasov said the report not only shows disrespect for the
status of Russian laws, but also neglects the human rights
practices of other nations. (Russia-US-Human Rights)
</P>
<P>
