<HEADLINE> Agassi to Play for United States against Russians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Former World No. 1 Andre
Agassi is backing to his form and may be leading the United States
against Russia when the two battle in a first-round Davis Cup
matchup.
</P>
<P>
"He certainly is strongly considering playing," Davis Cup
captain Tom Gullikson said. "He didn't commit 100 percent to it,
but obviously he has got some great feelings about Atlanta."
</P>
<P>
The three-day Davis Cup competition will be held April 3-5 at
Stone Mountain, Georgia, in the site where Agassi won the gold
medal in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Agassi had a disastrous 1997, falling to 141st in the world,
but is currently in the midst of a strong comeback that has seen
him raise his ranking to 71. In four tournaments since he began
his comeback, he has reached three finals, winning one. 
</P>
