<HEADLINE> Senior Citizens Express Innermost Feelings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Consulting agencies always
willing to listen to Shanghai's senior citizens have helped the
city's elderly people escape feelings of loneliness, sociologists
here said.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,200 consulting agencies in Shanghai, China's largest
commercial and economic center, provide comfort to senior
citizens.
</P>
<P>
Many of the agencies are staffed by highly educated elderly
people who discuss problems with those in need, offer advice and
help solve problems.
</P>
<P>
Other agencies seek to enrich the knowledge of senior citizens
in areas such as medicine, psychology, sociology and law, and some
offer household services.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that some 2.3 million elderly citizens at or
above the age of 60 account for 18.2 percent of the city's total
population.
</P>
<P>
"Shanghai currently faces pressing challenges related to its
aging population," sociologists said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
