<HEADLINE> China's Fishing Industry Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- China produced 36 million tons
of aquatic products in 1997, up 9.5 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Agriculture, during the
January-November period, the output of marine aquatic products of major
fisheries was 17.09 million tons, up 14.98 percent from the same
1996 period, and the output of fresh water products was 10.79 million
tons, up 15.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Last year, farmers also raised fish on 1.6 million hectares of
paddy fields, 15 percent up on 1996.
</P>
<P>
The ministry attributes the output increase to improved fishing
and cultivating techiques. 
</P>
