<HEADLINE> Environmental Protection Project Completed in Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- An environmental
protection project in central China's Henan Province has been put
into operation recently.
</P>
<P>
The Zhengzhou Golden Dragon Cement Co Ltd, the largest so far
in Henan, was built at a cost of 299 million yuan (37 million US
dollars). It produces 660,000 tons of cement a year, by consuming
200,000 tons of coal dust as raw materials.
</P>
<P>
The thermal power plants in Henan, with a combined generating
capacity of more than 10 million kilowatts, discharge a large
amount of coal dust every year, seriously polluting the
environment.
</P>
<P>
Environmental protection efforts have been made to see that the
project is environmentally-friendly, with six percent of the total
investment going to environmental protection sub-projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
