<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Govt Pledges Equal rights for Handicapped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina said that her government will ensure equal rights of the
country's handicapped people and their proper rehabilitation, the
national news agency BSS reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Handicapped people are not the burden of society rather they
can be turned into effective human resources through proper
nursing and care," Hasina said while addressing the inauguration
of the Center for the Rehabilitation of the Paralyzed (CRP) in
Dhaka Thursday.
</P>
<P>
One of the principal aims of the government was to ensure the
basic needs of the people including the handicapped through
eradicating poverty and illiteracy and creating job opportunities
for economic development, she added.
</P>
<P>
Many handicapped persons had been established in social life
after getting proper treatment, she said, adding that the Ministry
of Social Welfare would extend all-out help to the CRP in
conducting society-based rehabilitation activities aimed at giving
the healthcare service to the handicapped.  
</P>
