<HEADLINE> Dalian Hopes to Become China's Major Aquatic Products Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, a port city in northeast
China's Liaoning Province, is striving to become China's largest
Aquatic products base.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to achieve the goal in 1998 by cultivating
shellfish and other aquatic products on 65,000 ha of water
surface, according to Vice Mayor Jia Chongbin.
</P>
<P>
Jia said the city will introduce 360,000 rafts for aquatic
products cultivation this year.
</P>
<P>
Priorities will be placed on the application of advanced
techniques for the breeding of aquatic products, improvement of
marine species, and prevention of marine diseases.
</P>
<P>
Dalian harvested 1.66 million tons of aquatic products valued
at 6.2 billion yuan during 1997.
</P>
<P>
Dalian's 1997 export earnings for 150,000 tons of aquatic
products stood at 340 million U.S. dollars. 
