<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Tea Output Hits All-time High in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's tea output in 1997
reached an all-time high of 276.9 million kilograms, a seven
percent increase over the previous high of 258.4 million kilograms
in 1996, The Island newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, while the high and medium grown tea production showed
significant increases last year, production of low grown tea
dropped, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
High grown tea production in 1997 was 83.8 million kilograms,
compared with 72.2 million kilograms the previous year. Medium
grown tea production went up from 48 million kilograms in 1996 to
57 million kilograms last year.
</P>
<P>
Local tea experts have said this year's tea production might
encounter some difficulties due to a lasting draught which hit
this island nation early January.
</P>
<P>
Tea output this year could also be affected by the El Nino
phenomenon, they said.
</P>
<P>
Tea is a traditional export item of Sri Lanka.  
</P>
</TEXT>
