<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hke - IFC Launches Global Medium-Term Note Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 5 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation Thursday announced the launching of a one billion U.S.
dollar note issue under its Global Medium-Term Note program.
</P>
<P>
The five-year fixed-rate notes carry an annual coupon of 5.50
percent per annum and an issue price of 99.1246 percent to yield a
spread of 20 points over the US Treasury five-year benchmark.
</P>
<P>
The lead manager of the issue is Deutsche Bank Morgan
Grenfell. A group of nine additional financial institutions
completes the syndicate.
</P>
<P>
The latest transaction is IFC's largest single borrowing to
date. It brings IFC's market borrowings for fiscal year 1998,
which started July 1, 1997, to about 3.086 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group. It is the largest
multilateral source of financing for private sector projects in
developing countries. 
</P>
