<HEADLINE> Thailand to Open 32 More Businesses to Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Restrictions baring foreigners
from at least 32 business categories under Thailand's alien
business law would be lifted.
</P>
<P>
A working group set up by the Thai government to amend the law
has agreed that at least 32 business areas should be opened up to
allow 100 percent foreign investment, the local press reported
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of the Thai government's attempt to attract
back foreign investors to help salvage the country's flagging
economy.
</P>
<P>
A source at the Thai Commerce Ministry was quoted as saying
that the decision was reached in the middle of last week and has
been forwarded to a committee chaired by deputy prime minister and
commerce minister Supachai Panitchpakdi for consideration.
</P>
<P>
However, the working group, led by Sompol Kiatphaibool,
permanent secretary of the Commerce Ministry, has decided to
maintain restrictions in sensitive areas such as the country's
national resources, national security, ethics, the people's daily
life and health.  
</P>
