MADRID, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Spanish Prime Minister Jose
Maria Aznar said here Thursday that his country attaches great
importance to developing relations with China.
</P>
<P>
At an meeting with visiting Chinese Vice Premier Li Lanqing,
Aznar said that Spain will take positive steps to bring
Sino-Spanish relations closer.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Spain supports China's efforts to join the
World Trade Organization at an early date.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish prime minister said that many positive changes have
taken place in China over the past year and that Spain is watching
closely the rapid development of the Chinese economy.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the same occasion, Li said that since China and
Spain established diplomatic relations 25 years ago, great
progress has been made in friendly cooperation between the two
countries in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Over recent years, leaders from the two countries have
exchanged visits frequently, which contributed to further
development of bilateral relations, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side wishes to maintain the momentum of the
development of bilateral relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li also expressed hope that the two countries will make joint
efforts to promote economic, trade and scientific-technological
cooperation to higher levels.
</P>
<P>
Also Thursday, Li met with Spanish Foreign Minister Abel
Matutues to discuss relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li arrived in Madrid Wednesday on the four-day official visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
