<HEADLINE> Italian Industry Buoyant in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Italian industrial turnover
recorded a 5.8 percent increase in the first 11 months of 1997,
while orders were up 9.7 percent, the Italian Statistics Bureau
ISTAT reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sales went up by 10.5 percent abroad and by 3.8 percent on the
domestic market, said ISTAT.
</P>
<P>
Orders within Italy rose 7.3 percent, and those from abroad by
13.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The report showed that the annual sales of investment goods
went up 8.1 percent, intermediate goods by 5.7 percent and
consumer goods 4.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The strongest gain was made in the transport production sector
which increased sales by 25.9 percent. Metals and wood products
also surged.
</P>
<P>
Among orders, metals was the most buoyant sector showing a rise
of 16.8 percent, followed by machines and machine tools and
textiles and clothing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
