<HEADLINE> Brazilian Foreign Debt $193 Billion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, February 5 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian foreign
debt amounted to 193.094 billion U.S. dollars by the end of last
September.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian financial authorities announced that the foreign debt
increased eight percent, from 178.131 billion dollars in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The medium and long term debt went up 28 percent, from 55.661
billion dollars in 1996, to 71.275 billion dollars last
September. But the short-term debt went down 2.9 percent, from
28.807 billion dollars to 27.96 billion dollars during the same
period.
</P>
<P>
The authorities said that this year Brazil will have to pay
55.5 billion dollars to international banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
