<HEADLINE> Joint Settlement System Operates Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The new joint settlement
system between Shenzhen and Hong Kong handles 30 million yuan
in checks daily over the past month.
</P>
<P>
The system, introduced on January 5, has reduced the time
required for settlements between the Shenzhen Special Economic
Zone and the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region from
14 days to three days.
</P>
<P>
The system has also transformed the business scope from
international to intercity settlements.
</P>
<P>
The settlement system deals solely with Hong Kong dollar checks
used by Hong Kong businesspeople to pay for trade or labor services
provided by enterprises in Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Eight-five financial institutions in Shenzhen, including five
foreign banks, are participating in the operation. 
</P>
