<HEADLINE> China Pacific Insurance Records Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 6 (Xinhua) -- China Pacific Insurance
Co. Ltd. collected insurance premiums totalling 13.17 billion yuan
in 1997, a year-on-year rise of 50.3 percent, according to a
report General Manager Li Xueqian presented at Thursday's annual
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The total premium volume included property insurance of 5.62
billion yuan, up 2.78 percent, and life insurance of 7.55
billion yuan, up 129.59 percent.
</P>
<P>
Li attributed growing premiums to risk prevention for property
insurance and the improved structure for life insurance.
</P>
<P>
The company has enhanced its reputation by providing insurance
for a number of large projects, including the massive Three Gorges
Project, Xiaolangdi Dam and the Qinshan Nuclear Power Plant.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that China Pacific expects 1998 premiums to hit 15
billion yuan. 
