<HEADLINE> Beijing Development Zones Become Key Economic Growth Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 6 (Xinhua) -- In 1997, the combined
industrial output of development zones in Beijing was 25.1 billion
yuan, accounting for 14.6 percent of the city's total industrial
output, more than 6 times the figure of five years earlier.
</P>
<P>
Beijing now has 31 high-tech and economic development zones,
covering 256.6 sq.km. of ground. By the end of 1997, these zones
had 8,100 businesses, their investment totaling 58 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Rapid development of these zones is attributed to the quality
and efficiency of these enterprises, 80 percent of which are in
high-tech fields like electronic information, biological
engineering, new energy resources, and new materials.
</P>
<P>
Some 50 percent of Beijing's added industrial output value for
1997 resulted from new technologies.
</P>
<P>
The good investment environment was yet another factor in their
rapid development. The world's top 500 enterprises have put a
total of 2.2 billion US dollars into these development
zones. 
</P>
</TEXT>
