<HEADLINE> Chilean President's European Tour Ends in Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo Frei
returned to Santiago Thursday after ending his successful one-week
European tour.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Frei participated in the annual meeting of
the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland. He also visited
Spain.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean president said during the forum that the political
and economic stability of Chile has attracted more foreign
investments in the country.
</P>
<P>
Frei assured the forum delegates that Chile can weather the
financial crisis triggered by Southeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
In Davos, Frei met with his counterparts from Argentina and
Brazil to analyze the projections of the Southern Common Market
(Mercosur) in the new world economy.
</P>
<P>
"Mercosur has an important role in the world, and can provide
access to the Americas Free Trade Area, a Latin American vision
which could assist in the integration of the continent," he said.
</P>
<P>
In Spain, the governments of the two countries agreed to
accelerate negotiations to provide a free trade agreement between
Chile and the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean president guaranteed Spanish businessmen that his
country would remain politically, economically and socially stable.
</P>
<P>
Chilean Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Insulza said the visit
reflects the good relations with Spain and the EU. 
