<HEADLINE> Portugal Reiterates Support for Polish Membership in EU, NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Portuguese Foreign
Minister Jaime Gama on Thursday reiterated Lisbon's support for
Poland's efforts to join the European Union and NATO.
</P>
<P>
Gama, who ended a two-day official visit here Thursday,
repeated his pledge to approve the agreement on NATO's enlargement.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, signed last December by NATO and Poland,
Hungary and the Czech Republic, the three countries are to become
NATO members in April 1999.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Gama also met with Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski and parliamentary leaders, and exchanged instruments
with Polish Foreign Minister Bronislaw Geremek on avoidance of
double taxation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
