<HEADLINE> Qingdao to Open International School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao, a popular tourism city
in east China's Shandong Province, plans to open an international
school especially for the children of foreign nationals working
in the city.
</P>
<P>
The complex, which will be jointly established by the Qingdao
Education Commission and the Qingdao High-Tech Garden Management
Committee, will cover 1.16 hectares. The school building will
cover 4,000 sq.m. and will be constructed at a cost of 11.2
million yuan (1.39 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The school will operate in accordance with generally accepted
international norms in terms of staffing, materials, methodology,
equipment and administration.
</P>
<P>
The school will offer courses of English, Japanese and Korean and
various other languages. Graduates passing required examinations
will receive internationally authenticated diplomas. 
</P>
