<HEADLINE> Indonesia Concerned Over Tension in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 6 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
expressed its deep concern over the recent escalation of tension
in the Gulf and the threat of force against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The official Antara News Agency Friday quoted a press release
issued by the Foreign Ministry as saying that Indonesia was
calling on the parties concerned to exercise restraint and refrain
from using force, which will only pose a threat to world peace and
security.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia further called on the international community to make
every effort to address the situation by peaceful means aimed at
ensuring the effective implementation of weapons inspections in
Iraq in accordance with all relevant U.N. Security Council
resolutions, it said.  
