<HEADLINE> Young Scientists Play Important Role at Chinese University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, February 6 (Xinhua) -- Young scholars are playing an
important role in the Chinese University of Science and Technology
(CUST) in this capital city of Anhui Province, an important
theoretical research center in China.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 43 young scholars who are Outstanding Scholar Prize
winners in the university have been appointed heads of departments
or directors of research centers at the university. They have
raised 19 million yuan to fund various research projects.
</P>
<P>
The young scholars have also published more than 400 papers in
China and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Some of them have developed hi-tech projects and won national
and international awards.
</P>
<P>
