<HEADLINE> New Airport to Start Operating in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, February 5 (Xinhua) -- The De Pinto Martin
International Airport in Fortaleza, the capital of the Ceara
state, in the Brazilian northeast, will start operating soon, an
official source said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new De Pinto Martin International Airport structure which
follows the concept of "intelligent airports," has an area of
185,000 square meters and a capacity to receive 2.5 million
passengers a year.
</P>
<P>
The new airport has a bold and functional physical structure.
Its area of maneuvers and lateral runways are appropriate for
receiving 19 airliners simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
There are also in the airport two duty-free shops and a
shopping center that opens around the clock.
</P>
<P>
Brazil has now two other international airports: one in
Brasilia, the capital, and the other in Curitiba, the capital of
the Parana state, in the south of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
