<HEADLINE> Romania to Play Friendly Against Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, February 5 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian Soccer
Federation will try its best to guarantee the friendly between
Romania and Argentina being played as scheduled, according to
Romanian soccer official.
</P>
<P>
Mircea Sandu, president of the Romanian Soccer Federation, said
he would select the Romanian squad for the match together with
assistent coach Gavrila Bali. The match is scheduled on February
19 in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Romanian head coach Anghel Iordanescu, who will sign a contract
with Greek Soccer Federation later this week, has said that the
match would do no good to Romania's preparation for the World Cup
finals.
</P>
<P>
Romania and Argentina have both qualified for the World Cup
finals to be kicked off on June 10 in France. 
</P>
