<HEADLINE> South African Soccer Federation Fined for Late Registration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, February 5 (Xinhua) -- The South African Football
Association has been fined 3,000 U.S. dollars for registering late
for the African Cup of Nations Cup soccer tournament.
</P>
<P>
The South Africans are also denied two players as punishment
for late registerion, the Confederation of African Football
announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 22-man South African team was registered on Tuesday, only
four days instead of the 10 regulation days before the kick-off
competition in Burkina Faso.
</P>
<P>
The South African team will defend its title starting on Sunday
when it plays Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
