<HEADLINE> Wall Street Closes Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Stocks closed lower on
Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) featured by
profit-taking after a 223.21 point gain during the week.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 12.46 to 8,117.25 though
an early 52 point surge pushed the Dow within 80 points of its
highest close of 8,259.31 on August 6 last year.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 stock list fell 3.37 to 1,003.53
and the NYSE composite index dived 0.61 to 522.97 following three
sessions of record highs.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nastaq composite index was boosted by
computer-related stocks to cross the 1,700 point mark for the
first time since last October in early trading, but closed 3.54
lower to 1,676.90.
</P>
<P>
The small company dominated American Stock Exchange composite
index rose 2.53 to 677.00.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners 9-7 with 1,642 up, 1,255
down and 556 unchanged on the NYSE where trading volume totaled
699.18 million shares against 694.61 million shares previously.
</P>
