<DATE_TIME> 1998-02-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Independent Counsel Defends Lewinsky Probe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 5 (Xinhua) -- Independent counsel Kenneth
Starr, who is leading a probe into allegations of sex scandal
involving U.S. President Bill Clinton and former White House
intern Monica Lewinsky, said on Thursday the goal of his
investigation is to get at the truth.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in Little Rock, Arkansas, Starr refused
to discuss specific aspects of his probe, but he said it is "going
by the book" and making significant progress.
</P>
<P>
"We are going by the book. We want the truth, we want all the
truth. We want it completely, accurately, and we will satisfy
ourselves we are getting the truth. That is the absolute bedrock
point. We want the truth," Starr was quoted as saying by news
reports.
</P>
<P>
The independent counsel rejected allegations that his
investigation is politically motivated, saying, "Our job is to do
our job. It is not to engage in politics."
</P>
<P>
Starr also denied that any of the leaks in the case are coming
from his office, "but I share the concern with others about any
assault on the rule of the law."  
</P>
</TEXT>
